sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant Gateway as data-science-gateway<br/>(Envoy)<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant MLflow as MLflow Server<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS<br/>(service-ca TLS)
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS
    participant PG as PostgreSQL<br/>5432/TCP TLS
    participant S3 as S3-compatible Storage<br/>443/9000/TCP HTTPS

    note over Client,S3: Flow 1: External Client → MLflow via Gateway API

    Client->>Gateway: POST /mlflow/api/2.0/...<br/>Auth: Bearer SA Token<br/>TLS 1.2+
    Gateway->>MLflow: Forward to /api/2.0/...<br/>(path rewrite)<br/>TLS passthrough
    MLflow->>K8sAPI: SelfSubjectAccessReview<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token<br/>TLS 1.2+
    K8sAPI-->>MLflow: Authorization decision<br/>(mlflow.kubeflow.org pseudo-resources)
    MLflow-->>Gateway: API Response
    Gateway-->>Client: JSON Response

    note over MLflow,PG: Flow 2: MLflow → Backend Store

    MLflow->>PG: SQL queries (experiments, runs, models)<br/>PostgreSQL wire protocol<br/>PGSSLMODE=verify-full<br/>Auth: Connection string credentials
    PG-->>MLflow: Query results

    note over MLflow,S3: Flow 3: MLflow → Artifact Storage

    MLflow->>S3: PUT/GET model artifacts<br/>HTTPS (via CA bundle)<br/>Auth: AWS IAM credentials<br/>(from envFrom Secret)
    S3-->>MLflow: Artifact data

    note over K8sAPI,MLflow: Flow 4: Operator Reconciliation

    participant Operator as mlflow-operator<br/>controller-runtime

    K8sAPI->>Operator: Watch event (MLflow CR change)<br/>TLS 1.2+<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    Operator->>Operator: Render Helm chart<br/>with CR spec values
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Server-Side Apply (SSA patch)<br/>Deployments, Services, RBAC,<br/>NetworkPolicies, HTTPRoutes,<br/>ConsoleLinks, ServiceMonitors<br/>TLS 1.2+ / SA Token
    K8sAPI-->>Operator: Apply result
